snippet.textDisplay: Obviously from the low numbers this video is doing, team OVO has once again fumbled PND roll out. Would it kill these guys for Party to drop a video for once in his career that wasn’t drab, weird and underwhelming. This persona of being a Unicorn, never being present and a ghost is not appealing in this era especially not when you’re rolling out a project. The guys who Make a habit of ghosting e.g The Weeknd, Frank Ocean and Nas at least when it’s go time they’re hella present and go full force. For a jamming song like Loyal to be ensconced in a Visual of Play-dough animation is almost a slap on the consumer’s expectations and a disservice to PND’s Career. Soon enough without remedy, Party will forever lose touch with the wider globe and be restricted to a core loyal audience, pun intended. Forever missing the opportunity of being a true Global Superstar. How does an artist go from Party Volume 1 literally trapping the elixir of that ultimate Summer feeling to such a drop off that the music sounds like the dying days of fall and the distortion of early winter. Wow

snippet.textDisplay:
TEA (Conspiracy): Drake wrote the entire song. He has a history of writing songs, then giving it to others to sing because they're too personal. So this track is for Nicki Minaj, hence the uncanny Anaconda resemblance. The main character in the video and song isn't PND, it's Drake. Let's take a look at some of the lyrics. Written from Drake's perspective, he claims, "I don't want war with you or my friends." Nicki has went to war with the music industry, taking shot at Drake and his friends. Mainly his friends at Quality Control, who Nicki was beefing with. In the video, the Government (aka the music industry) is trying to get the big women out for over a year. The big woman represents Nicki's dominance within the music industry which the political establishment has tried to erase (Nicki vs Cardi). Drake was called in (maybe unknowingly on his part) to help get her out the rap game. In the video, PartyNextDoor (who is really Drake) accepts the mission and the money, but doesn't go through with 'taking her out' because she is his best friend. Other notable lyrics, "We spent the last three summers on our own," and "I got money on me and I'm loyal." Ima make it quick, im getting bored. around march 2017 nicki and drake were kinda still on good terms (no frauds vid). summer 2017, 2018, 2019. nada. they linked in summer 2018 before she dropped queen, but kept sending shots his way in "Dip" with Tyga, and in Good Form vid. Lastly, the reference the line with "I got money in my pocket, I'm loyal." I'm like why tf would a chick care about that, but the line references the break up with Nicki and Meek. The line was about Meek not having money in his pocket at the time when Nicki and Meek were out shopping for purses or jewelry or something mad expensive. So Meek asked Nicki to spot him. Nicki then checked Meek by name dropping that Drake would never, cause Drake be balling with his CASH IN HIS POCKET. Thus, "I got money on me and I'm loyal." Cause Meek cheated or something like that. yeaa
